articles.title: Legendary Australia captain quits international cricket after 7 World Cup titles - Hindustan Times
articles.description: Meg Lanning, who played six Tests, 103 one-day internationals and 132 Twenty20 internationals, will continue playing in the domestic cricket. | Cricket
articles.content:
Australia captain Meg Lanning has announced her retirement from international cricket after winning seven World Cup titles during a 241-match career.
